  "decision_conditions": [
    "REASON: The proposed fourth floor roof extension by reason of its inappropriate design, height, scale, and bulk is considered to form an overdominant and discordant feature. The proposal therefore fails to respect the character and appearance of the existing building and surrounding conservation area, resulting in an incongruous and disproportionate relationship with the adjoining building, harming the character and appearance of the Duncan Terrace/Colebrooke Row Conservation Area. Therefore the proposal is unacceptable, contrary to policy 12 of the National Planning Policy Framework (2012), policy 7.8 of the London Plan (2015), policy CS9 of Islington's Core Strategy (2011), policies DM2.1 and DM2.3 of Islington's Development Management Policies (2013) and guidance contained within the Conservation Area Design Guidelines (2002) an in particular paragraph 3.14 and the Islington Urban Design Guide (2006)."
